This project is a fork of 

https://github.com/peterwittek/mr-mpi-som-gpu

The input is a plain-text dense matrix, where the rows correspond to the instances.

You will need CUDA and MPI to compile the code.

Usage:
    [mpirun -np NPROC] somoclu [OPTIONs] INPUT_FILE OUTPUT_PREFIX
    Arguments:
         -e NUMBER     Maximum number of epochs
         -k NUMBER     Kernel type (default:
                          0: Dense CPU
                          1: Dense GPU
         -s            Enable snapshots U-matrix
         -x NUMBER     Dimension of SOM in direction x
         -y NUMBER     Dimension of SOM in direction y
    Examples:
         somoclu data/rgbs.txt data/rgbs
         mpirun -np 4 somoclu -k 0 -x 20 -y 20 data/rgbs.txt data/rgbs

The GPU setting method for a distributed system is based on GPMR by Jeff Stuart:
http://code.google.com/p/gpmr/
